This paper deals with the application of nonparametric image registration techniques to multisensor airborne remote sensing data for monitoring woodlands. The paper discusses the use of object recognition approaches for identifying individual trees, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also deals with the alignment of images obtained from different sensors, which is related to graphics (cs.GR) and image processing (cs.IR). The use of airborne remote sensing for monitoring woodlands involves robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IR, cs.RO, and cs.MM, in that order.
